then he falls like a ton of bricks.

23:43.440 --> 23:45.396
Stand back.

23:45.440 --> 23:50.116
We need an ambulance, please. The
Apollo restaurant, 23rd and Ninth.

23:50.160 --> 23:52.879
Is there a doctor here?

23:52.920 --> 23:55.150
Is anybody a doctor here?

23:55.200 --> 23:59.113
- You're dressed like a nurse.
- I'm a dental technician.

23:59.160 --> 24:02.436
- We're gonna need an ambulance.
- They're on the way.

24:02.480 --> 24:06.314
You gotta get him on his side
so he can breathe right.

24:06.360 --> 24:08.351
Where did you learn that?

24:08.400 --> 24:11.710
Campfire Girl...
I don't remember. Is he epileptic?

24:12.640 --> 24:15.313
- Yeah, I think...
- Sure? It could be drugs.

24:15.360 --> 24:18.955
Drugs? He don't look like
an addict to me. What is it?

24:19.000 --> 24:20.797
Epilepsy!

24:20.840 --> 24:25.197
Yeah, he's epileptic.
Go back to your tables, he's fine.

24:25.240 --> 24:27.629
The ambulance is coming. Thank you.

24:27.680 --> 24:31.150
Thanks for cooperating.
Free coffee for everyone.

24:31.200 --> 24:34.192
- Give everyone...
- Nick'll kill you.

24:34.240 --> 24:36.629
You can make that call now, Jorge.

24:37.920 --> 24:39.956
Your name is Frankie, right?

24:41.000 --> 24:42.991
- I'm Johnny.
- I know.

24:43.040 --> 24:45.076
Frankie And Johnny, the song.

24:45.120 --> 24:48.476
Yeah, I've heard of it.
Is he breathing all right?

24:48.520 --> 24:51.637
Yeah. Frankie and Johnny
were sweethearts...

24:51.680 --> 24:55.229
- I don't think he's breathing right.
- He's breathing.

24:55.280 --> 24:57.635
- Why not go out with me tonight?
- What?

24:58.360 --> 25:01.033
I'm asking you out with me tonight,
on a date.

25:01.640 --> 25:03.790
He just asked her out.

25:03.840 --> 25:06.912
- I don't believe this.
- What's not to believe?

25:06.960 --> 25:10.270
No. Keep him company.
I'll wait for the ambulance.

25:13.120 --> 25:16.351
- Welcome to the world.
- What happened?

25:16.400 --> 25:20.313
Nothing much. I just got
turned down by some woman.

25:20.360 --> 25:22.351
You're gonna be fine.

25:34.520 --> 25:36.431
Hey, Lucy.

27:50.080 --> 27:53.072
I'm actually in Rego Park.

28:02.320 --> 28:04.595
Look who's here.

28:08.760 --> 28:11.558
What's he doing here?
He didn't know her.

28:11.600 --> 28:14.876
Sure he did. His first day
was her last... I think.

28:14.920 --> 28:17.514
Helen can use all the mourners
she can get.

28:17.560 --> 28:19.869
- Nedda!
- I didn't mean it unkindly,

28:19.920 --> 28:22.559
I'm just glad
we didn't book St Patrick's.

28:22.600 --> 28:26.115
Tino and Luther were here earlier,
Nick got the flowers.

28:26.160 --> 28:28.435
- They're nice.
- I gotta go.

28:28.480 --> 28:32.075
I'm gonna go with you.
Funerals give me the willies.

28:32.120 --> 28:34.554
- You gonna come?
- We just got here.

28:34.600 --> 28:37.990
- It's the thought.
- I don't wanna leave her alone.

28:43.000 --> 28:44.991
Yeah, sure.

28:47.920 --> 28:51.799
Come on, Nedda, we don't need
a brick wall to fall on us.

28:51.840 --> 28:54.195
Shut up, don't be ridiculous.

28:55.240 --> 28:59.074
You're picking up a guy
in a funeral parlour

28:59.120 --> 29:01.998
in front of a freakin' stiff!

29:02.040 --> 29:05.555
In my wildest dreams
I didn't do anything like that.

29:05.600 --> 29:07.795
Blow it out your ass.

29:10.160 --> 29:12.037
Charming.

29:16.840 --> 29:18.876
Sorry, Helen.

30:10.520 --> 30:12.715
Who do I have to fuck
to get a waffle?

30:15.560 --> 30:17.357
Forget about the waffle.

30:18.440 --> 30:21.512
Thank you, Tino,
Oscar's a lot better.

30:21.560 --> 30:25.917
Hot plates, look out. Here's another
present for you, Luther.

30:32.760 --> 30:34.910
Can I ask you something?

30:35.960 --> 30:38.155
Yeah, shoot.

30:40.600 --> 30:43.398
Tino, give me a moment here.
Thank you.

30:45.160 --> 30:48.357
- I'll clean that later.
- Did you know Helen?

30:48.400 --> 30:52.109
- It looked like you were crying.
- Death is very sad.

30:53.680 --> 30:55.671
But you didn't even know her.

30:55.720 --> 31:00.191
You don't have to know someone to
feel sad for them. It's empathy.

31:00.240 --> 31:02.310
Yeah. Empathy, yeah.

31:02.360 --> 31:06.148
Empathy. The sympathetic vibrations
of two human beings.

31:06.200 --> 31:08.760
- I know what it means.
- No, you don't.

31:08.800 --> 31:11.519
I didn't know either
till I looked it up.

31:11.560 --> 31:15.348
You see, every day when I'm shaving,
I look up a new word.

31:19.600 --> 31:22.398
It's a little piece of turkey,
that's all.

31:22.440 --> 31:25.750
How can you have empathy
with someone you've never met?

31:25.800 --> 31:31.113
I didn't have to meet her. I just
looked at her picture and I knew.

31:32.040 --> 31:35.510
I knew she lived alone,
I knew she had these dreams

31:35.560 --> 31:38.870
that weren't quite enough
to keep her heart beating

31:38.920 --> 31:42.469
so she kept it going by
putting a bottle of Four Roses

31:42.520 --> 31:45.114
under her pillow - nobody knew about.

31:46.840 --> 31:49.035
Vodka.

31:49.080 --> 31:53.631
You should get a crystal ball and a
turban, you'd make a lot more money.

31:53.680 --> 31:58.435
I'm no fortune teller.
I just tell it the way I see it.

31:58.480 --> 32:03.395
She had that look. My mother
had that look her whole life.

32:03.440 --> 32:05.112
Disappointed.

32:06.160 --> 32:09.311
I need a blood sausage
and hash browns.

32:09.360 --> 32:11.669
Nedda! She's just asking me out!

32:11.720 --> 32:14.598
I am not! I am not asking you out.

32:17.200 --> 32:21.751
- I'm sorry I'm interrupting.
- You're slicing the turkey too thin!

32:27.200 --> 32:29.270
That's OK, I'll wait.

32:36.960 --> 32:39.838
Baby, you know
how I feel about you, right?

32:39.880 --> 32:41.950
Don't monopolise the phone.

32:53.720 --> 32:55.711
Thank you, Cora.

33:40.880 --> 33:43.030
Did you come?

33:43.080 --> 33:46.356
Yes. I usually
can hold it longer than that.

33:49.040 --> 33:52.510
- Sorry.
- But it didn't seem like you came.

33:55.440 --> 34:00.195
I came. I did. That was terrific.

34:01.840 --> 34:03.956
Are you sure?

34:04.000 --> 34:06.878
Are you kidding? Of course I did.

34:06.920 --> 34:10.993
Yeah, but usually a guy will moan
and yell or something,

34:11.040 --> 34:13.554
you didn't even clear your throat.

34:14.600 --> 34:16.955
I trained myself to do it quietly.

34:18.159 --> 34:22.915
- Why?
- Let's just say I've been in places

34:22.960 --> 34:27.670
where full-throated orgasm
would be highly inappropriate.

34:27.719 --> 34:31.507
- You mean like a monastery?
- Yeah, sort of.

34:34.920 --> 34:37.070
I'm dizzy.

34:39.239 --> 34:42.550
Maybe the shoes
was too much for you.

34:42.600 --> 34:44.591
It could have been.

34:44.639 --> 34:47.108
- Or position maybe.
- Position! Yes!

34:48.159 --> 34:51.469
I like that position.
Woman astride. Yes.

34:51.520 --> 34:55.399
Why didn't you say something?
I would have done it.

34:56.440 --> 34:59.796
You did it.
That's what this is, astride.

35:01.520 --> 35:04.512
- What, on top?
- Yeah, on top. Like this.

35:09.720 --> 35:12.075
Though my lips were sealed,

35:12.120 --> 35:16.113
my mind and my body
were just shooting off fireworks.

35:23.000 --> 35:25.434
So, it wasn't exactly perfect.

35:27.720 --> 35:29.711
Don't worry about it.

35:31.560 --> 35:36.998
I wasn't exactly 100% - these shoes
are cute but they kill my feet.

35:38.240 --> 35:40.231
Can I stay over?

35:44.720 --> 35:46.711
Why not?

35:46.760 --> 35:50.753
Because if you stay over, the two
of us will lay here all night, awake,

35:50.800 --> 35:54.509
pretending to be asleep but
wondering why we didn't hit it off.

35:55.560 --> 36:00.156
Johnny, you're just lonely.
I'm just lonely.

36:01.280 --> 36:03.874
We don't have to be Romeo and Juliet.

36:07.200 --> 36:09.191
Lonely.

36:11.600 --> 36:13.955
You got a boyfriend, you said.

36:15.160 --> 36:19.392
I got two boyfriends.
I'm looking for one Mr Right.

36:30.000 --> 36:33.356
- I'll see you tomorrow.
- See you at the salt mines.

36:33.400 --> 36:35.470
- Bye.
- Good night.

36:41.120 --> 36:44.157
- It's not the end of the world.
- I know.

36:46.200 --> 36:48.589
I seen the end of the world.

36:57.960 --> 37:01.999
"But look, the morn,
in russet mantle clad

37:02.040 --> 37:06.431
"Walks o'er the dew
of yon high eastward hill."

37:06.480 --> 37:09.836
- The morn?
- What the hell does it mean?

37:09.880 --> 37:11.950
It means the sun is up.

37:12.000 --> 37:15.197
Why doesn't he just say so
instead of this bullshit?

37:15.240 --> 37:18.516
Because he's Shakespeare.
The greatest poet ever.

37:19.160 --> 37:21.754
Are you saying
you don't respect me any more?

37:21.800 --> 37:25.110
- I could care less!
- I don't respect you any more.

37:25.160 --> 37:27.435
I think you're both a pair of tramps.

37:27.480 --> 37:30.677
Look, I did you both a favour,
I tried him out.

37:32.000 --> 37:33.991
Did he really...?

37:35.440 --> 37:38.159
Two minutes tops!

37:38.200 --> 37:41.590
- I hate that!
- And so quiet. Like a mouse.

37:41.640 --> 37:44.518
Marcel Marceau
comes louder than this guy.

37:44.560 --> 37:48.030
Maybe you scared him.
That isn't out of the question.

37:48.080 --> 37:50.913
Well, maybe so
but I don't read poetry.

37:50.960 --> 37:54.077
As I see it, you need two words
to make it in this town -

37:54.120 --> 37:56.111
"fuck" and "you".

37:56.160 --> 38:00.278
- Someone didn't get laid last night.
- I get laid every night.

38:00.320 --> 38:02.276
I bet you do.

38:03.600 --> 38:06.876
- No, not the wig!
- No! I knew not to use the wig.

38:06.920 --> 38:10.993
Do you know those gold pumps I got?
The stilettos? I put 'em on,

38:11.040 --> 38:13.713
things are looking good,
but then I...

38:20.680 --> 38:22.830
I know what you two
are talking about.

38:22.880 --> 38:24.677
- You do?
- Of course I do.

38:24.720 --> 38:27.314
What are we talking about?
Say the word.

38:27.360 --> 38:30.432
- Leave her alone.
- Just one time. Just for me.

38:30.480 --> 38:34.553
- Copulate. Say it.
- Cora, leave her alone.

38:34.600 --> 38:37.273
- Once in your life.
- You are so mean!

38:37.320 --> 38:41.199
You can do it! On the count of three.
One, two, three!

38:41.240 --> 38:43.231
I watch Dr Ruth.

38:46.600 --> 38:48.511
Peter, telephone.

38:48.560 --> 38:50.835
Yeah. How much?

38:54.280 --> 38:56.077
What's with you?

38:59.360 --> 39:02.875
Ladies and gentlemen, staff,
I have an announcement.

39:02.920 --> 39:06.833
- Crazy busboy.
- I sold my first script.

39:06.880 --> 39:10.077
Right! They're flying me
first class to sunny LA

39:10.120 --> 39:12.680
to begin shooting Bloods On The Moon!

39:13.720 --> 39:16.518
I'll give you one last day
and I'm off to Hollywood.

39:32.720 --> 39:35.075
Son of a bitch! Pardon my French.

39:37.840 --> 39:39.910
Nice shot.

39:40.800 --> 39:43.758
OK, serving for the game,
this is it.

39:45.080 --> 39:47.036
I got you now! Go, Joe!

39:47.080 --> 39:49.719
Shit! Pardon my French.

39:53.480 --> 39:56.313
- Out!
- There it is, good game. Good game.

39:56.360 --> 39:59.716
- Good one, Joe.
- I gotta go catch criminals.

40:06.320 --> 40:09.790
Why won't you go to
Peter's going-away party with me?

40:11.000 --> 40:13.833
- I don't want to.
- I'll pick you up at seven.

40:13.880 --> 40:17.555
- Sometimes you're really obnoxious.
- I'm not obnoxious.

40:17.600 --> 40:21.434
I'm just eager to go out with you.
That's a big difference.

40:21.480 --> 40:23.869
545 West 54th Street, right?

40:24.800 --> 40:27.712
- How do you know that?
- Come on, it's on your punchcard.

40:27.760 --> 40:31.878
What are you doing looking at
my punchcard? You stay away from it.

40:31.920 --> 40:34.036
What's your apartment number?

40:38.280 --> 40:40.874
- 6A.
- No, I don't believe you.

40:51.480 --> 40:54.472
6B? 3F? Am I close?

40:54.520 --> 40:57.717
- Am I talking to myself over here?
- Just a minute.

40:57.760 --> 41:01.799
What can I do to make you respond
to me? Can I write little notes?

41:01.840 --> 41:03.910
I don't respond to little notes.

41:03.960 --> 41:07.509
- What about if I give you presents?
- You can afford that?

41:07.560 --> 41:11.269
- I'm saying little.
- I don't like presents and things.

41:11.320 --> 41:15.518
I know, I gonna back off
but I gotta tell you something.

41:15.560 --> 41:18.996
- I got a crush on you.
- Burger Deluxe, pick up.

41:20.520 --> 41:22.511
Why do you want to go out with me?

41:22.560 --> 41:25.358
Because the heart does things
for reasons

41:25.400 --> 41:27.789
that reason cannot understand.

41:27.840 --> 41:30.877
Does Nick know about this?
I'm gonna tell Nick.

41:30.920 --> 41:34.390
You got her jealous, you see?
You got her all riled up.

41:34.440 --> 41:37.398
I want to know why
you want to go out with me.

41:37.440 --> 41:40.955
We're gonna go to the party
and walk in alone?

41:41.000 --> 41:43.389
Our whole life
we spend alone at parties.

41:43.440 --> 41:47.115
So we walk in together,
it's not so bad. So bad?

41:49.440 --> 41:52.000
No, it's not. We can do it.

41:53.040 --> 41:56.555
- What? Do what?
- What's the matter?

41:56.600 --> 41:59.319
I don't even remember
what my order was!

41:59.360 --> 42:03.433
One meatloaf platter
and two chef's salads.

42:04.480 --> 42:06.471
See? I never forget an order.

42:06.520 --> 42:10.559
Cancel the tuna melt, the customer
just died of malnutrition.

42:10.600 --> 42:13.319
I'm giving his lawyer
your number, OK?

42:29.000 --> 42:32.436
Try something a little more festive.
You need these?

42:33.080 --> 42:34.957
No, not yet.

42:36.880 --> 42:39.553
I'm too old for this shit.

42:39.600 --> 42:41.477
Come on.

42:44.280 --> 42:48.637
- You look like an Italian widow.
- I wish you'd just come with me.

42:48.680 --> 42:52.559
I can't. I've cancelled this dinner
three times already.

42:52.600 --> 42:54.670
I hate going to parties alone.

42:54.720 --> 42:57.712
I always feel like
everybody's staring at me.

42:57.760 --> 43:01.912
Dressed in that they probably are.
What time is the bullfight?

43:01.960 --> 43:04.110
Let me weave my magic spell.

43:06.440 --> 43:10.069
The land of lost dresses.
And the winner is...!

43:11.880 --> 43:16.192
There. Now that is a party dress.
I feel prettier already.

43:16.240 --> 43:19.835
If you don't want to go
to parties alone, start dating again.

43:19.880 --> 43:23.509
She hasn't had a date in three years.
Not since Phillip...

43:23.560 --> 43:26.711
- I said the "Ph" word.
- It's not true.

43:26.760 --> 43:29.991
What about that Welshman?
I dated him that whole summer.

43:30.040 --> 43:32.031
Please! I don't count him.

43:32.080 --> 43:34.674
What? He asked me to marry him.

43:34.720 --> 43:38.872
That's why I didn't like him.
I knew he wouldn't leave his wife.

43:38.920 --> 43:41.275
What do you know about those things?

43:41.320 --> 43:44.471
- More than you do obviously.
- She doesn't have to date.

43:44.520 --> 43:46.590
I don't date by choice.

43:46.640 --> 43:49.029
Too bad because I love your choices.

43:49.080 --> 43:51.640
We went from Mr Abuse You
to Mr Use You,

43:51.680 --> 43:55.798
plus a fling with a cross dresser
that I blew the whistle on.

44:00.240 --> 44:05.030
Yes! Mama, the pumps. Definitely
the pumps. Bobby, what do you think?

44:05.080 --> 44:08.755
- Leave me out of it.
- I'm giving us six weeks.

44:10.720 --> 44:12.790
Are you expecting someone?

44:16.480 --> 44:18.471
Hello, who is it?

44:21.920 --> 44:25.230
I just got goosebumps.
Do you know that song?

44:27.040 --> 44:28.758
Four weeks.

44:28.800 --> 44:33.271
It says your name but it doesn't
say the apartment number.

44:33.320 --> 44:37.199
- 6A. What?
- It's the new guy at work. The cook.

44:37.240 --> 44:39.595
- Is he cute?
- Yeah, sort of.

44:39.640 --> 44:42.757
Do you have a date with him
or did you order sandwiches?

44:42.800 --> 44:45.872
No, he asked me to go out with him
and I told him no

44:45.920 --> 44:49.390
then he asked me to Peter's party
and I said no, I think.

44:49.440 --> 44:51.476
What did I say?

44:51.520 --> 44:55.115
How should I know? Who cares?
It's a gentleman caller.

44:57.120 --> 45:00.317
What did he do? Run up?
This guy means business.

45:00.360 --> 45:02.351
- Should I get it?
- Wait!

45:03.160 --> 45:04.957
Who are you gonna say you are?

45:05.000 --> 45:09.516
The Man Who Shot Liberty Valance!
What's wrong with you? How do I look?

45:09.560 --> 45:12.996
- I'm supposed to say that!
- Yeah, but you never do.

45:15.080 --> 45:17.594
My God! I look like the Breck girl.

45:21.320 --> 45:23.470
- This is 6A, right?
- 6A.

45:23.520 --> 45:25.715
- Welcome.
- Hello.

45:27.000 --> 45:29.389
- Are you OK?
- My God!

45:30.520 --> 45:32.988
- Can I get you something?
- I'm fine.

45:33.800 --> 45:35.950
I just ran up five flights.

45:37.160 --> 45:40.789
I don't know what got into me,
I just had to run up.

45:40.840 --> 45:44.116
- Wanted to get here.
- You didn't have to do that.

45:44.160 --> 45:46.310
No, it was my pleasure.

45:48.400 --> 45:50.391
- So, you ready?
- Almost.

45:50.440 --> 45:51.998
Yeah? Good.

45:52.040 --> 45:54.600
Nice apartment. Big for a studio.

45:55.760 --> 46:00.436
OK, sit. I guess there's
not an empty chair in the house.

46:04.480 --> 46:07.836
Man, I couldn't figure out
what to wear either.

46:14.480 --> 46:18.439
This is Tim and Bobby,
they're hooking up my VCR.

46:18.480 --> 46:20.277
Right.

46:22.400 --> 46:25.233
I'm Tim, he's Bobby.
I live across the hall

46:25.280 --> 46:28.272
and Bobby lives with
the Von Trapp family.

46:29.600 --> 46:31.750
So, this is your first date?

46:34.480 --> 46:36.675
We just started dating ourselves.

46:39.640 --> 46:42.029
Each other?

46:44.680 --> 46:47.717
That's interesting.
You'd never know it.

46:56.320 --> 47:00.438
This is really nice and homey.
Elephants!

47:00.480 --> 47:03.074
She's collected those
since she was kid.

47:03.120 --> 47:06.192
When the trunks are up,
it means good luck.

47:06.240 --> 47:08.310
But they gotta face the window.

47:09.640 --> 47:12.837
Otherwise it's bad luck.
I read that somewhere.

47:12.880 --> 47:15.269
That explains a lot.

47:18.680 --> 47:21.240
I think I could help you
with that wire.

47:21.280 --> 47:25.876
I think I got it if I could just...
Sure you know what you're doing?

47:25.920 --> 47:28.957
Last time I worked on one of these...

47:30.000 --> 47:32.230
OK, I think
that one goes right there.

47:32.280 --> 47:35.352
- I'm sure.
- No, it goes over here.

47:37.240 --> 47:39.754
You gotta take the plug...

47:39.800 --> 47:42.951
- Are you an electrician?
- No, I'm a cook.

47:45.240 --> 47:48.357
This is so exciting.
I feel like your big sister.

47:49.400 --> 47:52.551
- What do you think?
- He's nice.

47:53.560 --> 47:55.994
That's a rotten thing to say!

47:56.040 --> 47:59.271
He's very nice.
Look, we've both done worse.

48:00.320 --> 48:03.630
Of course, he could be
a mass murderer or a psycho.

48:03.680 --> 48:05.955
Thank you for sharing that with me.

48:06.000 --> 48:09.037
Come on,
hurry up before he changes his mind.

48:09.080 --> 48:11.275
It's better the way I had it.

48:11.320 --> 48:13.311
Yeah, I think you're right.

48:13.360 --> 48:16.955
Maybe I should just learn to leave
well enough alone.

48:17.920 --> 48:21.196
Let me help you. Here. Try this.

48:24.960 --> 48:27.599
I have a cousin who's gay,
by the way.

48:32.240 --> 48:34.800
- Most people do.
- Ready?

48:34.840 --> 48:37.434
- He's a really great guy.
- I'm sure.

