01:15:48.000 --> 01:15:50.275
- Why not?
- They don't like it.

01:15:50.320 --> 01:15:51.912
Do you need help?

01:15:51.960 --> 01:15:56.670
How would you like it if Nedda said
she loved you and wanted your baby?

01:15:57.720 --> 01:16:01.633
Nedda, I really like you,
you're nice but I love Frankie.

01:16:01.680 --> 01:16:04.319
- I'm getting help.
- You don't know me.

01:16:07.000 --> 01:16:09.514
I can't do anything,
I slept with the guy.

01:16:09.560 --> 01:16:12.677
- You slept with him?!
- Frankie didn't tell you?

01:16:12.720 --> 01:16:14.950
She said you slept
with everybody else.

01:16:15.000 --> 01:16:18.197
- She didn't mention the gold pumps?
- He wore gold pumps?

01:16:20.240 --> 01:16:22.231
You just wanna believe that.

01:16:22.280 --> 01:16:24.635
It makes it easier for you
to run away.

01:16:24.680 --> 01:16:26.750
"You don't know me."

01:16:26.800 --> 01:16:29.473
I don't know you? I know you.

01:16:29.520 --> 01:16:32.318
What do you want, Frankie?
What do you want?

01:16:32.360 --> 01:16:34.476
What do you want from a guy?

01:16:34.520 --> 01:16:37.398
I want a guy who will love me
no matter what.

01:16:37.440 --> 01:16:39.317
You got him. Here. Me.

01:16:39.360 --> 01:16:41.920
This is worse than
Looking For Mr Goodbar.

01:16:42.960 --> 01:16:46.953
I am trying to improve my life
and I'm running out of time.

01:16:48.000 --> 01:16:51.151
Find someone else
who is double-parked like you.

01:16:51.200 --> 01:16:54.237
It could happen.
I could meet somebody tomorrow.

01:16:54.280 --> 01:16:57.636
- Get laid, think I was in love.
- Don't let me stop you.

01:16:57.680 --> 01:17:01.195
You're not stopping me,
I'm stopping me. I love you.

01:17:01.240 --> 01:17:05.153
But I'm so scared.
So scared you are gonna retreat back.

01:17:05.200 --> 01:17:08.272
You know, that place
you're so comfortable with,

01:17:08.320 --> 01:17:11.392
that place where nobody can find you.

01:17:11.440 --> 01:17:13.635
That's why I'm coming on so strong.

01:17:13.680 --> 01:17:15.591
What's going on here?

01:17:18.680 --> 01:17:24.038
Frankie, chances like this
don't come along often.

01:17:24.080 --> 01:17:28.119
You gotta take 'em because
if you don't, they're gone forever.

01:17:29.160 --> 01:17:32.152
And you may wind up not only -

01:17:32.200 --> 01:17:35.033
and pardon my French
for the very last time -

01:17:35.080 --> 01:17:37.548
screwing some other person you meet,

01:17:37.600 --> 01:17:41.673
thinking you're in love with
this person and marrying them.

01:17:41.720 --> 01:17:44.188
- It happens.
- OK, you're making her cry.

01:17:44.240 --> 01:17:46.913
Boy, are you barking up
the wrong tree!

01:17:47.960 --> 01:17:50.520
I never thought
I could fall for a woman

01:17:50.560 --> 01:17:52.949
who said "barking up the wrong tree".

01:17:53.000 --> 01:17:55.878
- Let's go.
- You've driven me to it!

01:17:55.920 --> 01:18:00.516
All right, let's calm down, shall we?
Wait outside. Are you all right?

01:18:00.560 --> 01:18:04.394
I've never used
that expression. Ever!

01:18:04.440 --> 01:18:06.237
If I wanted a man in my life,

01:18:06.280 --> 01:18:09.192
I wouldn't have bought a VCR
I can't even work.

01:18:44.640 --> 01:18:46.790
Excuse me...

01:18:48.520 --> 01:18:52.308
I live in the building
across from you and...

01:18:54.600 --> 01:18:56.989
I've seen how he beats you.

01:19:00.800 --> 01:19:03.189
Is there anything I can do?

01:19:04.240 --> 01:19:07.277
I don't know
what you're talking about.

01:19:38.120 --> 01:19:40.111
Shit!

01:19:43.080 --> 01:19:45.753
Excuse me.
Don't be afraid, let me help.

01:19:46.800 --> 01:19:48.791
Thanks, mister.

01:20:24.280 --> 01:20:28.751
I can't take it any more. You're not
giving up your job because of him.

01:20:28.800 --> 01:20:31.519
You were there first.
I'll handle him.

01:20:33.200 --> 01:20:35.509
Now, what's the problem?

01:20:35.560 --> 01:20:39.269
He says he's in love with me.
He wants to marry me.

01:20:39.320 --> 01:20:42.153
- Bastard!
- He's talking about a family.

01:20:42.200 --> 01:20:46.079
You can pick 'em. Love, a home,
marriage? Screw that shit.

01:20:47.120 --> 01:20:49.714
- Can I answer this?
- Tell him to go to hell.

01:20:51.000 --> 01:20:54.310
Frankie just said something
very derogatory about you

01:20:54.360 --> 01:20:56.635
but I know at least a dozen women

01:20:56.680 --> 01:21:00.309
and quite a few men
I can put you in touch with.

01:21:00.360 --> 01:21:03.352
Johnny, give it a rest.
She doesn't want to talk.

01:21:04.400 --> 01:21:06.470
He wants to know about tonight.

01:21:06.520 --> 01:21:09.876
Saturday night,
the loneliest night of the week.

01:21:11.360 --> 01:21:14.158
I'm busy, call me in a few years.

01:21:15.440 --> 01:21:17.590
He's singing.

01:21:20.800 --> 01:21:25.078
I got to go, we're expecting
another call from you any minute.

01:21:29.640 --> 01:21:33.110
Remember, you're new here
so you're easy to fire.

01:21:33.160 --> 01:21:37.472
OK, keep things clean. Over here,
we have the ice for the drinks.

01:21:37.520 --> 01:21:40.830
Remember that. Here's the telephone,
don't use it.

01:21:40.880 --> 01:21:46.034
I like your ponytail. You don't
write scripts? All dishes go here.

01:21:46.080 --> 01:21:49.277
Over here, all waitresses
put dirty dishes here.

01:21:49.320 --> 01:21:50.912
You keep clean.

01:21:50.960 --> 01:21:52.951
- You're going to kill me.
- Why?

01:21:53.000 --> 01:21:57.471
Many people changing shifts. It makes
me dizzy. It's not my fault, OK?

01:22:01.960 --> 01:22:05.236
- You had tonight off.
- So did you.

01:22:05.280 --> 01:22:07.430
Yeah, well, something came up.

01:22:07.480 --> 01:22:09.755
Something came up for me too.

01:22:12.200 --> 01:22:15.078
Look, I don't wanna hurt
your feelings, OK?

01:22:15.120 --> 01:22:19.671
I really don't but Nick doesn't like
the help messing around.

01:22:19.720 --> 01:22:24.271
So please, don't make this difficult,
I really need this job.

01:22:24.320 --> 01:22:27.198
You think I would
jeopardise your job?

01:22:27.240 --> 01:22:30.630
I'd quit before I'd do that,
I mean that. And I need this job.

01:22:30.680 --> 01:22:34.036
OK, let's just both
go about our business.

01:22:36.480 --> 01:22:40.393
A chicken sand' and
it's birthday time at table eight.

01:22:40.440 --> 01:22:43.477
This is new cashier
and she's my grandmother.

01:22:43.520 --> 01:22:47.149
You give her check when you finished.
Come.

01:22:47.200 --> 01:22:49.395
Good, have good time.

01:22:55.080 --> 01:22:58.197
- Happy birthday, Uncle Lou.
- You look great!

01:22:58.240 --> 01:23:00.231
Lou, blow it out.

01:23:04.440 --> 01:23:07.716
- Thank you.
- Grilled cheese and skins.

01:23:07.760 --> 01:23:11.070
I got a little carried away
at the bowling alley.

01:23:11.120 --> 01:23:16.274
My errand didn't turn out too good,
so I'm sorry, I apologise.

01:23:16.320 --> 01:23:18.754
You certainly made an impression.

01:23:22.560 --> 01:23:24.551
You want something to drink?

01:23:27.640 --> 01:23:32.873
I'm on a break too, so...
talk, don't talk, it's up to you.

01:23:54.040 --> 01:23:56.634
Are you keeping
some big secret from me?

01:23:56.680 --> 01:23:59.990
- Like what?
- Like I don't know, you tell me.

01:24:02.520 --> 01:24:04.875
- I'm not married.
- Were you?

01:24:04.920 --> 01:24:06.911
Yes.

01:24:08.160 --> 01:24:11.550
- How many times?
- Once. That it?

01:24:12.600 --> 01:24:14.591
Were you in jail?

01:24:16.600 --> 01:24:20.354
- I served 18 months in the slammer.
- What for?

01:24:20.400 --> 01:24:23.995
Signing somebody else's name
to somebody else's cheque.

01:24:24.040 --> 01:24:28.795
- A forger?
- I'd call it a failed forger.

01:24:29.840 --> 01:24:31.831
I just did it once, I was...

01:24:33.360 --> 01:24:35.794
Is that where you
did all your reading?

01:24:35.840 --> 01:24:37.637
Yeah, most of it.

01:24:37.680 --> 01:24:40.274
I got most of my books
from Henry Hank Hill.

01:24:41.360 --> 01:24:44.272
- Don't know him.
- Nobody did.

01:24:44.320 --> 01:24:49.348
He was executed two months ago.
I cooked him his last meal.

01:24:52.880 --> 01:24:56.714
- This lettuce is limp.
- I'm sorry, you're right.

01:24:56.760 --> 01:24:58.910
I'm going to the john.

01:24:58.960 --> 01:25:01.554
How about you?
Were you ever married?

01:25:02.360 --> 01:25:05.830
No. Chef's salad, chicken salad
and a side of 'slaw.

01:25:05.880 --> 01:25:08.189
- Anyone serious?
- Try terminal.

01:25:08.240 --> 01:25:11.152
Who's this serious person?

01:25:12.560 --> 01:25:16.235
He got more serious with
who I thought was my best friend.

01:25:16.280 --> 01:25:21.070
- Really? How long ago was that?
- Three years.

01:25:23.960 --> 01:25:28.238
I was divorced three years ago.
Now, is that a coincidence?

01:25:28.280 --> 01:25:31.397
- Really?
- I cross my heart and hope to die.

01:25:31.440 --> 01:25:34.352
- Waitress!
- I'll be right with you, ma'am.

01:25:38.400 --> 01:25:40.630
- You got any kids?
- Two.

01:25:40.680 --> 01:25:42.750
I thought so. You see 'em?

01:25:43.800 --> 01:25:46.837
- Yesterday. First time in two years.
- Yeah?

01:25:46.880 --> 01:25:48.916
That's what the errand was.

01:25:48.960 --> 01:25:51.758
My wife remarried,
she lives in the suburbs.

01:25:51.800 --> 01:25:55.270
- I hate the suburbs.
- It's not bad. Beautiful house.

01:25:55.320 --> 01:25:59.438
Nice. I could never have provided
them with anything like that.

01:25:59.480 --> 01:26:02.916
I got there, there were my kids,
playing on the lawn.

01:26:02.960 --> 01:26:05.155
I bet they were glad to see you.

01:26:09.440 --> 01:26:13.149
I didn't get out of the car,
you know. I just couldn't...

01:26:20.080 --> 01:26:23.470
They looked so happy and all.
They got so big.

01:26:24.800 --> 01:26:27.268
Looked like somebody else's kids.

01:26:29.240 --> 01:26:31.231
I just drove away.

01:26:35.480 --> 01:26:38.836
It's like I lost them, you know?
That's how I feel.

01:26:38.880 --> 01:26:42.634
- Waitress!
- Hello? Can we get some service?

01:26:42.680 --> 01:26:46.070
You haven't lost them,
you're just not ready.

01:26:49.640 --> 01:26:52.871
Finally! What's safe to eat here?

01:26:52.920 --> 01:26:55.388
I'm sorry, we're closed.

01:26:56.640 --> 01:26:58.631
What kind of a place is this?

01:27:03.440 --> 01:27:05.670
Hurry up, let's go.

01:27:05.720 --> 01:27:09.474
- Night, Frankie.
- Night, Andreas.

01:27:09.520 --> 01:27:12.114
Here's yours, Frankie.

01:27:12.160 --> 01:27:15.550
- You come back any Saturday night.
- Thanks, Maxine.

01:27:15.600 --> 01:27:17.591
- Night, Maxine.
- Night.

01:27:18.640 --> 01:27:21.712
Was she home? Did you talk to her?

01:27:21.760 --> 01:27:25.196
- What she say?
- I'm seeing the kids next weekend.

01:27:27.160 --> 01:27:29.151
- Good.
- Thank you.

01:27:32.440 --> 01:27:34.431
What is that?

01:27:35.480 --> 01:27:37.471
It's a rose.

01:27:38.480 --> 01:27:40.471
Grew in the kitchen.

01:27:44.320 --> 01:27:46.311
Good night, closing up.

01:27:46.360 --> 01:27:50.353
Everything finished. It's good.

01:27:50.400 --> 01:27:52.197
What's that?

01:27:53.240 --> 01:27:56.038
- It's potato.
- It's a rose.

01:27:56.080 --> 01:27:58.514
- Johnny made it.
- On my break.

01:27:59.560 --> 01:28:01.391
It's nice.

01:28:01.440 --> 01:28:03.829
Red potato, it's very romantic.

01:28:05.440 --> 01:28:07.431
Frankie, you want lift home?

01:28:07.480 --> 01:28:09.516
It's OK. Thanks.

01:28:16.000 --> 01:28:19.276
OK, you know how to close up.
Bring back fork.

01:28:20.960 --> 01:28:23.155
- Good night.
- Night, Nick.

01:28:24.120 --> 01:28:27.351
Come on, Grandma,
we go home and watch wrestling.

01:28:29.960 --> 01:28:32.758
Come on, I'll walk you home.

01:28:33.240 --> 01:28:37.438
So, how about you? Do you ever
want to kill yourself sometimes?

01:28:38.600 --> 01:28:41.797
Yeah, everybody wants
to kill themself sometime.

01:28:41.840 --> 01:28:44.115
Can we change the subject?

01:28:44.160 --> 01:28:46.549
- You want me to buy you that?
- Yeah.

01:28:51.360 --> 01:28:55.717
If you had any wish,
what you wish to be?

01:28:55.760 --> 01:28:58.069
You won't laugh?

01:28:58.120 --> 01:29:02.033
- Teacher. Teaching little kids.
- That's good.

01:29:02.080 --> 01:29:05.436
What about you?
Did you always dream of being a cook?

01:29:05.480 --> 01:29:08.278
No, prison did it.

01:29:08.320 --> 01:29:12.711
When I went in and I heard
that "clank", you know, I died.

01:29:13.880 --> 01:29:17.714
Then they put me in the kitchen
with food and, I don't know,

01:29:17.760 --> 01:29:19.796
suddenly I was born again.

01:29:19.840 --> 01:29:24.038
I started to feel
like I could breathe again.

01:29:24.080 --> 01:29:27.356
You know,
it was like I had aspirations.

01:29:27.400 --> 01:29:30.597
Aspiration?
Have you been shaving again?

01:29:32.560 --> 01:29:35.950
So what about this
terminal relationship you had?

01:29:36.000 --> 01:29:39.959
What was it? A guy who left you
for your best friend?

01:29:40.000 --> 01:29:43.834
Phillip? You know what
the main thing I felt was? Dumb.

01:29:43.880 --> 01:29:47.759
I even introduced them.
I lent them money.

01:29:47.800 --> 01:29:49.791
I gave her my old television.

01:29:50.840 --> 01:29:53.559
They're probably watching it
right now.

01:29:53.600 --> 01:29:56.558
I hope it explodes and blows
their faces off.

01:29:58.640 --> 01:30:02.155
What about before Phillip?
Anybody else?

01:30:02.200 --> 01:30:04.919
I don't wanna talk about that.

01:30:16.360 --> 01:30:18.920
OK, but you can't spend the night.

01:30:23.040 --> 01:30:25.679
There's gotta be
something in this world

01:30:25.720 --> 01:30:30.077
better than watching you do that
but I'm damned if I know what it is.

01:30:30.120 --> 01:30:31.712
Yeah, sure.

01:30:31.760 --> 01:30:35.912
No, I'd put it up there.
It's a vision, inspired spectacle.

01:30:35.960 --> 01:30:39.316
I'd put it up there with
the Grand Canyon,

01:30:39.360 --> 01:30:42.909
mother nursing her child,
triumphant facts of nature.

01:30:42.960 --> 01:30:46.669
- You been to the Grand Canyon?
- I have not, no.

01:30:46.720 --> 01:30:50.474
Me either. I'd like to go there
some day. Hawaii, too.

01:30:53.720 --> 01:30:55.711
Open your robe.

01:30:59.440 --> 01:31:01.795
No, I don't wanna open my robe.

01:31:03.040 --> 01:31:04.837
Why?

01:31:04.880 --> 01:31:07.348
I don't know,
I just wanna look at you.

01:31:11.240 --> 01:31:13.196
15 seconds, that's all.

01:31:13.240 --> 01:31:17.597
- I just wanna look at it.
- Look at what? Why?

01:31:19.200 --> 01:31:22.829
I don't know, I just...
To know that I can.

01:31:22.880 --> 01:31:25.917
That I can look at the woman I love
and just see her.

01:31:25.960 --> 01:31:29.350
Her eyes, her breasts,
her stomach, her...

01:31:29.400 --> 01:31:32.631
- Don't say it! I hate that word.
- I wasn't going to.

01:31:32.680 --> 01:31:35.148
I hate both of them!

01:31:35.200 --> 01:31:38.317
I'll look up some new ones
in my thesaurus.

01:31:42.280 --> 01:31:45.556
I never know when you're
playing games or being serious.

01:31:45.600 --> 01:31:48.990
It's both. Serious games.
Why do we have to name everything?

01:31:49.040 --> 01:31:53.556
Say you had a pet parakeet. If it was
beautiful, I'd want to look at it.

01:31:53.600 --> 01:31:56.717
You'd let me look at it
and we'd move on.

01:31:56.760 --> 01:32:00.150
I had a parakeet, I hated it.
I was glad when it died.

01:32:14.840 --> 01:32:18.958
15 seconds. I'm timing this.
Turn that light out.

01:32:42.960 --> 01:32:47.272
I told my cousin I didn't want a
bird. She swore I'd love a parakeet.

01:32:47.320 --> 01:32:49.788
What's to love?
They don't do anything

01:32:49.840 --> 01:32:53.469
except not sing when you want them to
and sing when you don't

01:32:53.520 --> 01:32:55.909
and make that awful scratching noise.

01:32:55.960 --> 01:33:00.397
If I ever get another pet,
it'll be a dog.

01:33:01.400 --> 01:33:03.470
Something you can hold.

01:33:04.520 --> 01:33:08.308
The only time I got my hands on
that parakeet was the day it died

01:33:08.360 --> 01:33:12.148
and I had to pick it up
and throw it away. That's enough.

01:33:12.200 --> 01:33:15.397
That's got to be 15 seconds.
Happy now?

01:33:27.440 --> 01:33:29.510
That music is nice.

01:33:31.280 --> 01:33:35.751
It makes me think of grace.

01:33:37.360 --> 01:33:39.430
This is Midnight With Marlon.

01:33:39.480 --> 01:33:43.109
For information on becoming
a member of the WNYL family,

01:33:43.160 --> 01:33:46.709
why not give me a call? 555-1111.

01:33:48.800 --> 01:33:52.475
Why do you want to kill
yourself sometimes?

01:33:52.520 --> 01:33:56.718
I want to kill myself when I think
I'm the only person in the world

01:33:56.760 --> 01:34:01.834
and that part of me that feels
that way is trapped inside this body

01:34:01.880 --> 01:34:04.110
that only bumps into other bodies

01:34:04.160 --> 01:34:09.109
without connecting to another person
in the world trapped inside of them.

01:34:11.480 --> 01:34:13.550
We have to connect.

01:34:14.560 --> 01:34:16.551
We just have to.

01:34:17.760 --> 01:34:22.470
I feel... very...

01:34:22.520 --> 01:34:24.431
Say it.

01:34:25.480 --> 01:34:27.835
- I don't know what.
- Say it anyway.

01:34:27.880 --> 01:34:30.952
- Protective.
- Good. That's very nice.

01:34:31.000 --> 01:34:34.754
I'm looking for somebody
to take care of me this time.

01:34:34.800 --> 01:34:36.836
Aren't we all?

01:34:38.720 --> 01:34:42.599
Why do we keep going from one subject
I don't like to another?

01:34:44.320 --> 01:34:46.959
What is this?
Suddenly the armour's up?

01:34:47.000 --> 01:34:48.718
What about your armour?

01:34:48.760 --> 01:34:53.390
Besides, I wasn't talking about you.
Not everyone thinks life is a picnic.

01:34:54.120 --> 01:34:58.398
Some of us have problems.
Some of us have sorrows.

01:34:58.440 --> 01:35:01.432
People like you
are so busy telling us what you want

01:35:01.480 --> 01:35:03.471
you don't notice the rest of us

01:35:03.520 --> 01:35:06.353
who aren't exactly singing
Yankee Doodle Dandy.

01:35:06.400 --> 01:35:09.278
Hold it, how we getting
into this now?

01:35:09.320 --> 01:35:11.470
I've done nothing but notice you.

01:35:11.520 --> 01:35:13.397
You don't, you smother me.

01:35:13.440 --> 01:35:16.955
I'm not giving up everything
for someone I don't know.

01:35:17.000 --> 01:35:19.230
I can't repeat the same stupidity.

01:35:19.280 --> 01:35:23.239
Who says you have to give up
anything? We're talking about love.

01:35:23.280 --> 01:35:26.192
- We're not in love.
- That's what you think.

01:35:26.240 --> 01:35:30.074
I think we are. Just because
you've given up on that possibility

01:35:30.120 --> 01:35:32.873
there's no need to drag me down
to that level.

01:35:33.720 --> 01:35:36.553
I think you better leave now.

01:35:36.600 --> 01:35:40.275
You know, I'm sorry.
I thought you were a kindred spirit.

01:35:41.240 --> 01:35:44.630
Kindred means two of a kind
sharing a great affinity.

01:35:44.680 --> 01:35:48.878
- I know what kindred means.
- Shall we go for affinity?

01:35:49.920 --> 01:35:55.995
You know, that is the first really
rotten thing you've said to me.

01:35:56.040 --> 01:36:02.479
To make fun of somebody else's
intelligence or education or lack of,

01:36:02.520 --> 01:36:05.318
that is somebody
I'd be very glad not to know.

01:36:05.360 --> 01:36:07.396
I thought you were sad, weird.

01:36:07.440 --> 01:36:10.113
- I didn't know you were cruel.
- I'm sorry.

01:36:10.160 --> 01:36:14.517
It's just a cruelty waiting
to happen again. I want you to go.

01:36:14.560 --> 01:36:16.915
Why do you want me to go? Really.

01:36:16.960 --> 01:36:19.679
I want to be alone,
I want to watch my VCR,

01:36:19.720 --> 01:36:21.915
eat ice cream, I want to go to sleep.

01:36:21.960 --> 01:36:27.557
Come on, alone? Sooner or later
you're gonna have to deal with us.

01:36:27.600 --> 01:36:29.830
There's just no two ways about it.

01:36:30.640 --> 01:36:34.235
So why don't we just get it
over with? You're in the mood.

01:36:34.280 --> 01:36:38.034
Tomorrow's Sunday, day off.
We'll sleep in. Let's talk.

01:36:38.080 --> 01:36:40.071
- Right, I'm calling Tim.
- Tim?

01:36:40.120 --> 01:36:42.634
No, Bobby.
He'll beat the shit out of you.

01:36:42.680 --> 01:36:45.877
- Not yet.
- I'll open that window and scream.

01:36:45.920 --> 01:36:49.959
In this city? Everybody's doing
the same thing, who'll hear you?

01:36:51.160 --> 01:36:53.515
Get out!

01:37:01.160 --> 01:37:04.072
I promise I will go
only I wanna make a call.

01:37:07.480 --> 01:37:14.238
You know, this all should be so easy.
Why is it always so damn hard?

01:37:17.040 --> 01:37:23.559
Hello? Midnight With Marlon?
Hello, Marlon. My name is Johnny

01:37:23.600 --> 01:37:28.720
and I would like to know the name
of that piece of piano music

01:37:28.760 --> 01:37:30.751
you were playing a minute ago

01:37:30.800 --> 01:37:33.314
so I can buy the record
for my lady love,

01:37:33.360 --> 01:37:37.478
whose name is Frankie, is that
a coincidence? Frankie and Johnny.

01:37:39.200 --> 01:37:43.716
Debussy, Claude Debussy, right.
Clair de Lune, you got that?

01:37:44.720 --> 01:37:46.950
Why are you doing this?

01:37:48.000 --> 01:37:50.673
Everything I want is in this room.

01:37:54.640 --> 01:37:56.631
Hello, Marlon?

01:37:57.720 --> 01:38:02.157
I know you don't take requests
but could you just listen to me?

01:38:02.200 --> 01:38:05.237
Now, there's a man and a woman.

01:38:05.280 --> 01:38:07.748
He's a cook, she's a waitress.

01:38:09.080 --> 01:38:11.833
Now, they meet
and they don't connect,

01:38:11.880 --> 01:38:17.432
only she noticed him,
he could feel it, and he noticed her

01:38:17.480 --> 01:38:20.199
and they both knew
it was gonna happen.

01:38:20.240 --> 01:38:25.155
They made love
and for maybe one whole night,

01:38:25.200 --> 01:38:27.430
they forgot the 10 million things

01:38:27.480 --> 01:38:31.109
that make people think
"I don't love this person,

01:38:31.160 --> 01:38:34.152
"I don't like this person,
I don't know this..."

01:38:34.200 --> 01:38:37.749
Instead, it was perfect
and they were perfect

01:38:37.800 --> 01:38:40.473
and that's all there was
to know about it.

01:38:40.520 --> 01:38:43.318
Only now, she's beginning
to forget all that

01:38:43.360 --> 01:38:45.430
and maybe he'll forget it, too.

01:38:45.480 --> 01:38:48.517
So could you play an encore
for Frankie and Johnny

01:38:48.560 --> 01:38:53.350
in the hope of something that ought
to last and not self-destruct?

01:38:57.160 --> 01:39:00.914
Why don't you just
think about it? Thank you.

01:39:09.680 --> 01:39:12.069
I want to show you something.

01:39:26.320 --> 01:39:28.788
That guy I didn't want to talk about,

01:39:28.840 --> 01:39:31.400
he did this with a belt buckle.

01:39:40.960 --> 01:39:42.951
It's gone.

01:39:44.480 --> 01:39:46.436
It'll never go.

01:39:46.480 --> 01:39:49.313
It's gone. I made it go.

01:39:49.360 --> 01:39:52.909
No, Johnny, you can't make it
go away. Nobody can.

01:39:56.720 --> 01:39:58.870
He's the reason I can't have...

01:40:01.280 --> 01:40:03.271
kids.

01:40:10.080 --> 01:40:12.275
He knocked me around

01:40:16.600 --> 01:40:19.194
when I was pregnant and...

01:40:22.440 --> 01:40:24.829
I lost the baby.

01:40:26.400 --> 01:40:28.789
There were complications.

01:40:35.880 --> 01:40:37.871
He's gone now.

01:40:39.320 --> 01:40:42.517
I would never hit you. Never.

01:40:45.120 --> 01:40:47.509
You don't have to be afraid any more.

01:40:47.560 --> 01:40:49.676
I am. I'm afraid.

01:40:51.520 --> 01:40:55.274
I'm afraid to be alone,
I'm afraid not to be alone.

01:40:55.320 --> 01:40:59.233
I'm afraid of what I am,
what I'm not,

01:40:59.280 --> 01:41:02.477
what I might become,
what I might never become.

01:41:06.000 --> 01:41:10.790
I don't wanna stay at my job
for the rest of my life but I...

01:41:15.160 --> 01:41:17.720
I'm afraid to leave.

01:41:17.760 --> 01:41:22.709
And I'm just tired, you know,
I'm just so tired of being afraid.

01:41:29.800 --> 01:41:32.030
Honey, listen.

01:41:34.600 --> 01:41:39.674
I know I can't make the bad go away.
You're right, I can't.

01:41:41.440 --> 01:41:45.035
But when the bad comes again...

01:41:46.960 --> 01:41:49.155
I'm gonna be next to you.

01:41:53.960 --> 01:41:55.951
I can't, Johnny.

01:42:01.000 --> 01:42:02.797
I'm sorry.

01:42:33.720 --> 01:42:36.917
This is WNYL in New York

01:42:36.960 --> 01:42:40.157
and you're listening to
Midnight With Marlon.

01:42:40.200 --> 01:42:43.476
As you know, it's not my policy
to take requests

01:42:43.520 --> 01:42:46.592
but there's always
an exception to the rule.

01:42:46.640 --> 01:42:51.760
I don't know if this is the most
beautiful song, Frankie and Johnny.

01:42:51.800 --> 01:42:54.189
I wish they
really were your names

01:42:54.240 --> 01:42:56.879
but I know when
my leg's being pulled.

01:42:57.920 --> 01:43:00.559
God, how I wish you two
really existed.

01:43:00.600 --> 01:43:04.195
Maybe I'm crazy, but I'd still
like to believe in love.

01:43:04.240 --> 01:43:06.231
Why the hell do you think
I work these hours?

01:43:10.080 --> 01:43:14.756
Anyway, you two moonbeams,
whoever, wherever you are,

01:43:14.800 --> 01:43:16.916
whatever you're doing,

01:43:16.960 --> 01:43:19.269
this one's for you.

01:43:19.320 --> 01:43:21.470
Here's an encore.

01:44:40.800 --> 01:44:43.155
You wanna brush?

01:44:46.040 --> 01:44:48.395
That means you want me to brush?

01:44:52.160 --> 01:44:54.879
Take the blue one,
it's never been used.

01:47:05.560 --> 01:47:07.835
I'm not gonna ask whose robe this is.

01:47:08.680 --> 01:47:10.671
Good.

01:47:19.720 --> 01:47:22.837
You should get toothpaste
with fluoride.

01:47:22.880 --> 01:47:24.871
Listen.

01:47:33.600 --> 01:47:35.591
No matter what?

01:47:49.120 --> 01:47:51.156
I'm 36.

